Package: AutoXplainR
Title: Guided Model Fitting, Evaluation, and Explanation
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person(
      given = "Matteo",
      family = "Mazzarelli",
      email = "matteo.mazzarelli@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
Description: Guides first-time modelers through fitting, held-out evaluation,
    explanation, and communication for tabular prediction problems. Safe local
    defaults compare an understandable model with a simple baseline and define
    every reported metric. Training-only resampling can tune behaviorally
    diverse linear, regularized, additive, tree, forest, boosting, neural,
    kernel, nearest-neighbor, and multivariate adaptive regression spline families
    without opening the final holdout. Model-agnostic tools compare predictive
    disagreement and fitted reliance across families, and add repeated
    permutation importance, feature-dependence diagnostics, accumulated local
    effects, and provenance-rich evidence audits. Optional adapters support
    'H2O' AutoML, interactive 'Plotly' graphics, and evidence-constrained
    narratives.
